content:
Full of unique characters, Yumekui Merry has everything to get a second season soon enought. I stumbled upon this one because of Merry and could create some expectations when I first read the name. Saving dreams and destroying nightmares? Seems amazing, right? It indeed is, but a little more develpoment was missing on this one...
{STORY - 6/10}
Despite John Doe stealing the spotlight during first episodes, he somehow wasn't a big matter on the rest of the story. Yumeji is able to "detect" what John said to be "vessels", humans that share their bodies with mumas ("dream demons"), enabling them to vome to our world. Meetingwith Merry was the first of his problems, since he was dragged to all this dream trouble thanks to her.


Both Yumeji and Merry are special: he's able to access other people's dreams freely and she doesn't need a vessel to leave the Dream World. Main objetive they both have now is to stop Pharos Hercules, a powerful muma able to lead the others, like a guiding light. He has a brief appearance, like John. Maybe both will be more present on a possible second season...


And we have that small cliche of taking over the world and everything. Pharos wants to replace all humanking by mumas, destroying everyone's dreams and hopes. Only thing that makes it different is that most mumas are interested on the real world. They want to see people's dreams and protect them from those trying to destroy them...


{ART - 5/10}


Since this anime features a good share of action scenes, it's expected to have really thrilling moments, but movements were poorly developed on most occasions. I wasn't able to feel the adrelanine... However, scenarios were very well designed, with a realistic effect that made them so original.


{SOUND - 7/10}


Retro-like background sounds are played oftenly, mostly on daydream scenes. Still, I felt a lack of effects on battle scenes and that was a little lame. Other than that, a really nice eletro song was featured on ED themes!


{CHARACTER - 6/10}


Many different mumas are featured in here, with unique personalities and shared interests. The weakest ones, like Pallette just want to know about humans' dreams, while stronger mumas, like Engi and Leon, want particular kinds of revenge. While Engi is a good muma, that tries to protect humans, Leon remains neutral, in order to accomplish his side objective. Evil ones, like Pharos and Mistletainn don't care about their actions and have separate ambitions.


As for the other characters, Yumeji is overally weak, but is strong-willed and believes that every muma in here is able to return to the Dream World. Merry is a girl who doesn't recall about her past and want answers from other mumas. That's why she needs to leave the real world, despite no knowing how to do it.


{ENJOYMENT - 7/10}


It was a good anime, but I didn't fell amazed, unlike others I've watched before. The plot is really good, but it lacks emotion. Still, it was really enjoyable. However, I was a little disappointed with the ending... Could be better...


{OVERALL - 6/10}


Dreams shown in here are something everone holds onto. They are hopes, a reason to live so, without them, we're nothing, we have no ambitions. That's where Yumekui Merry makes her entrance, to "eat" all bad dreams and stop mumas with evil intentions. A hero with the sole objective of knowing who she is, now with a mission: to keep people dreaming and hoping. Future depends on our dreams, abstract things that give us strenght to move foward and be happy within ourselves.
